32:33.900 --> 32:36.660
OK, why should we study the brain?

32:36.660 --> 32:39.340
First most obvious reason, know thyself.

32:39.340 --> 32:42.780
Know what this thing is that's operating in our heads.

32:42.780 --> 32:46.340
This is who you are, right, is your brain.

32:46.340 --> 32:51.900
There are lots of very fine and important organs in the body,

32:51.900 --> 32:54.380
but the brain is special, right?

32:54.380 --> 32:58.500
So a heart is important, you die without it,

32:58.500 --> 33:01.860
but it's the brain that's your identity, right?

33:01.860 --> 33:05.340
So there's a reason that surgeons do heart transplants.

33:05.340 --> 33:06.140
That makes sense.

33:06.140 --> 33:09.460
Something wrong with your heart, you need another heart, OK?

33:09.460 --> 33:11.660
But why don't they do brain transplants?

33:11.660 --> 33:13.420
That wouldn't make sense, right?

33:13.420 --> 33:15.260
If there's something wrong with my brain,

33:15.260 --> 33:17.740
it doesn't make sense to take someone else's brain

33:17.740 --> 33:20.260
and put it in here, because then I'd be that other person.

33:20.260 --> 33:23.540
It doesn't make sense, because the brain is who you are.

33:23.540 --> 33:24.980
OK, so the brain is really special.

33:24.980 --> 33:27.740
It's not just another organ.

33:27.740 --> 33:30.780
That's why a few years ago we had the decade of the brain,

33:30.980 --> 33:33.860
not the decade of the pancreas or the liver or the kidney, right?

33:33.860 --> 33:35.100
People need to study these things.

33:35.100 --> 33:37.060
They need to know how to fix them.

33:37.060 --> 33:41.780
They're important, but they're not as cosmic as the brain, OK?

33:41.780 --> 33:48.500
All right, second reason why we should understand brains,

33:48.500 --> 33:52.220
and that is to understand the limits of human knowledge.

33:52.220 --> 33:54.900
Like the more we understand about the human mind,

33:54.900 --> 34:00.020
the more we can actually evaluate how good our knowledge is.

34:00.020 --> 34:03.420
Are there things that we might not be able to think?

34:03.420 --> 34:05.460
Possible true scientific theories,

34:05.460 --> 34:08.220
we might not be able to understand ever?

34:08.220 --> 34:09.900
You can think of studying the mind

34:09.900 --> 34:12.580
as a kind of empirical epistemology,

34:12.580 --> 34:15.060
a way to actually know about the knower

34:15.060 --> 34:18.900
so we can figure out how good the knowledge is in that knower.

34:18.900 --> 34:20.820
So that's another reason.

34:23.180 --> 34:25.980
A third reason is to advance AI.

34:25.980 --> 34:28.380
And so up until a few years ago, I

34:28.380 --> 34:29.820
used to give lectures on vision,

34:29.820 --> 34:33.460
and they would all start with some version of this.

34:33.460 --> 34:36.540
You guys all have amazing visual abilities

34:36.540 --> 34:38.620
in the back third of your brain that does vision.

34:38.620 --> 34:40.300
You can do all this incredible stuff

34:40.300 --> 34:42.540
that no machine can touch.

34:42.540 --> 34:43.740
That's off to you.

34:43.740 --> 34:46.300
You have an amazing visual system back here,

34:46.300 --> 34:50.180
and those guys in AI, it is mostly guys, guys, gals, whatever,

34:50.180 --> 34:53.580
those people in AI, could only dream

34:53.580 --> 34:55.860
of coming up with algorithms as good as the one that's

34:55.860 --> 34:59.300
running in the back of your head.

