35:06.940 --> 35:09.380
been a massive revolution.

35:09.380 --> 35:12.500
And all of a sudden, deep nets are

35:12.500 --> 35:15.020
doing things that are really close to human abilities,

35:15.020 --> 35:17.020
particularly in vision.

35:17.020 --> 35:20.140
So for example, in visual object recognition,

35:20.140 --> 35:23.180
machines were way far behind human vision

35:23.180 --> 35:28.860
until very recently, especially when this paper here came out,

35:28.860 --> 35:31.700
was published in 2012.

35:31.700 --> 35:34.660
First author, Khrushchevsky, it has now

35:34.660 --> 35:37.540
been cited an astonishing 33,000 times.

35:37.540 --> 35:39.420
Actually, I made this slide a couple of weeks ago.

