So what's so important about this paper?

36:00.220 --> 36:02.980
Well, they trained, as probably most of you know,

36:02.980 --> 36:06.820
they trained a deep net on the over a million images

36:06.820 --> 36:11.140
in ImageNet, a massive computer database of images.

36:11.140 --> 36:14.340
And they basically taught it to do object recognition.

36:14.340 --> 36:16.660
And it performed much more accurately

36:16.660 --> 36:21.340
than any previous system, and it approaches human abilities.

36:21.340 --> 36:24.380
So this is major, this is a radical change in the situation

36:24.380 --> 36:26.140
that we were in five years ago.

36:26.180 --> 36:27.780
So things have changed radically.

36:27.780 --> 36:30.820
So just as an example, here's one

36:30.820 --> 36:33.500
of the figures from that seminal paper.

36:33.500 --> 36:36.260
So here is one of the images from ImageNet

36:36.260 --> 36:40.500
that AlexNet, this trained network, was tested on.

