And Madagascar, cat, et cetera.

37:48.580 --> 37:50.260
So pretty amazing.

37:50.260 --> 37:54.220
And nothing even close to this was possible before 2012.

37:54.220 --> 37:55.580
So this is very recent history.

37:55.580 --> 38:00.140
And it has totally shaken up the field in lots of ways.

38:00.140 --> 38:01.740
And so that's been transformative,

38:01.740 --> 38:03.620
not just for computer science, but it's also

38:03.620 --> 38:07.260
been transformative for cognitive science and neuroscience.

38:07.260 --> 38:10.260
Because now we have algorithms, like here's this deep net,

38:10.260 --> 38:11.860
and it does this thing.

38:11.860 --> 38:14.660
So that's a possible theory of how humans do it.

38:14.660 --> 38:18.140
It's a possible computationally precise theory

38:18.140 --> 38:19.460
of what's going on in here.

38:19.460 --> 38:20.660
And we didn't used to have those.

38:20.660 --> 38:22.820
And now we have those for a number of domains.

38:22.820 --> 38:24.540
And that's shaking up the field.

38:24.540 --> 38:26.220
There will be a whole lecture on deep nets

38:26.220 --> 38:29.060
and how you can use them to think about minds and brains

